JOHANNESBURG - Anti-Semitic graffiti was found spray-painted on a building at the University of Witwatersrand on Tuesday. The South African Union of Jewish Students (SAUJS) released a statement on their Facebook page condemning the action. READ:Â But is it hate speech? The organisation also recounted an incident that reportedly occurred on campus, two weeks prior, where a student was "verbally accosted with anti-Semitic remarks" "There can be no justification for such hateful, ignorant and offensive acts," SAUJS stated. The student organisation has been in contact with the office of the Dean of Students to ensure that the graffiti be removed and to find those responsible. The Muslim Students Association tweeted their condemnation of the hate speech found on campus on Tuesday afternoon eNCA